The paper proposes a parallel algorithm for the earliest arrival time problem on public transport networks, which involves processing temporal graphs with departure times and durations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to algorithms, data structures, artificial intelligence, social and information networks, and networking and internet architecture. Specifically, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories given the focus on parallel algorithms and pruning techniques. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories given the use of general-purpose programming and the application to public transport networks. Finally, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a potential category given the use of temporal graphs and connections in a public transport network context.
